  "doc_id": "40656",
  "text": "The effects of SA on environmental stress responses have also been reported. In maize (Zea mays), treatment with SA suppressed drought tolerance [CITATION_1] . In Arabidopsis, the growth of wild-type plants was suppressed by SA accumulation below 58C. However, NahG plants, which are unable to accumulate SA, can grow better than wild-type plants under these conditions [CITATION_2] . Similarly, NahG plants are more resistant to NaCl treatment [CITATION_3] ). These results suggest that SA plays a role in inhibiting environmental stress responses, which supports our finding that the activation of SAR suppresses environmental stress responses.",
